HIV/Aids: China ta ce an samu karuwar sabon kamuwa da cutar da kashi 14 cikin 100
Kasar Sin ta ce ta samu karuwar kashi 14 cikin dari na yawan mutanen da ke rayuwa da cutar HIV da AIDS.
Bisa ga ƙididdigar gwamnati, an yi wa mutane fiye da 820,000 kamuwa da cutar a ƙasar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na 2018, an samu kusan sababbin shari'o'i 40,000.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka sun kasance ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ya nuna canji daga baya.
A wasu wurare a ƙasar Sin, an yi amfani da jini don yaɗa cutar.
Amma, an rage yawan mutanen da suka kamu da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar zuwa kusan sifili, kamar yadda masana kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin suka ce a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Yawan mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da AIDS a kasar Sin ya karu da mutane 100,000 a kowace shekara.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An yi watsi da jima'i a kasar Sin a shekara ta 1997, amma an ce har yanzu ana nuna bambanci ga LGBT.
Domin yawan mutanen da ke cikin wannan ƙasar, an kiyasta cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin 100 na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza suna aure.
Yawancin cututtuka na wannan cuta sun fito ne daga rashin kariya ta jima'i a cikin waɗannan dangantaka.
Tun shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin Sin ta yi alkawarin samun cikakken maganin cutar HIV a matsayin wani ɓangare na ƙoƙarin magance wannan matsalar.
